<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-298-102  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 298 102.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  March 27 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>New for IBM: Russian language translator for the PC. (frommicroTrans) (product announcement)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   microTrans (product introduction).andO;Product:   Linguist (Computer program) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     Software PublishersProduct IntroductionLanguage TranslationSoftware packages.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>NEW FOR IBM: Russian Language Translator for the PC LIVERMORE, CALIFORNIA,U.S.A., 1990 MAR 23 (NB) -- Linguist, from microTrans, is a foreign language,word-by-word, translation system that includes a bilingual text editor withmany word-processing features; a translator; and a complete set ofdictionary, editing, and maintenance routines.andM;Other features include a user-definable keyboard; RAM-loaded dictionaries forfast translation; on-line help screens; choice of batch or immediatetranslation mode; user-group support with dictionary exchange privileges; andOCR program compatibility.andM;Linguist updates dictionaries when given new translations and allowsmodification of existing dictionary entries during translation sessions.andP;  Theprogram translates in either direction.andM;Linguist can be run through its own menus or directly through DOS 3.0 orlater; it requires an EGA or VGA display and .andM;The program currently supports the H-P LaserJet and compatible printers andprints foreign language files using graphics modes on IBM graphics printersand Epson-FX printers.andP;  Software and system files require 1.2 megabytes ofdisk space; file storage requirements vary with dictionary size but average300 Kbytes.andM;Linguist is now available with English/Russian language support for $285through April 30, after which the same package will sell for $385.andP;  Withlanguage fonts but no dictionaries, the system sells for $245; after April30, $345.andP;  Additional supported languages sells for $95; additionaldictionaries cost $60.andP;  An English/Russian demo disk is available for $5.andO;Call 415-447-0596 for more information.andM;(Computer Currents/19900323)</TEXT></DOC>